description:
Although Anna Moffo's voice was not large, it was warm and rich, with soft pastel colorings and a velvety and extended range. Agile coloratura technique allowed her to sing high soprano bel canto repertory magnificently, especially "Lucia di Lammermoor." 
Her great beauty gave her the nickname "La Bellissima".
